<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-3-1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Introduction</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      The <m>n^{\text{th}}</m>
      order linear differential equations are of the form
    <men xml:id="eq-nonhomogeneous-0">
  \phi^{(n)}(x) + a_{n-1}(x)\phi^{(n-1)}(x) + \cdots + a_1(x)\phi'(x) + a_0(x)\phi(x) = f(x)
    </men>
        </p>
<p>
  where the functions 
  <m>a_0(x), \dots, a_{n-1}(x), a_n(x)</m> 
  and 
  <m>f(x)</m> 
  are continuous on some interval <m>I</m>.
</p>
    



</introduction>
</section>